<leg xml:space="preserve" billnum="HB0563" sponsor="David Shallenberger" designation="HB" otherSponsor="" otherHouse="Senate" sess="2026GS" fileno="2026FL1267" date="2/13/2026 10:02:767" printDate="02-13 10:00" subVer="0" minVer="0" office="LEGISLATIVE GENERAL COUNSEL" actionDate="" impact="code"><info><nextbuid>9</nextbuid><aminfo anum="0" effdate="05/06/2026"><seclist><sect action="E" src="code" buid="6" uid="C58-55-S308.2_2026050620260506" sort="58 55 03080220260506" mtype="section" effdate="05/06/2026">58-55-308.2</sect><sect src="uncod" untype="effdate" buid="8" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" mtype="uncod" effdate="05/06/2026"/></seclist></aminfo></info><tbox><sinfo><nextpairid>0</nextpairid></sinfo><st numlevel="1" lineno="1" slineno="0-1">Radon Amendments</st><sessionhead>2026 GENERAL SESSION</sessionhead><statehead>STATE OF UTAH</statehead><sponsorhead>Chief Sponsor: David Shallenberger</sponsorhead><otherSponsorhead>Senate Sponsor: </otherSponsorhead></tbox><lt numlevel="1" lineno="2" slineno="0-2"><lthead lineno="3">LONG TITLE</lthead><gdhead lineno="4">General Description:</gdhead><gd numlevel="1" lineno="5" slineno="0-5">This bill creates a new section in the Utah Construction Trades Licensing Act governing <ln numlevel="1" lineno="6" slineno="0-6"/>radon mitigation.</gd><hphead lineno="7">Highlighted Provisions:</hphead><hp numlevel="1" lineno="8" slineno="0-8">This bill:<hl numlevel="1" lineno="9" slineno="0-9" level="1">requires a person that installs, repairs, maintains, cleans, or replaces a radon mitigation <ln numlevel="1" lineno="10" slineno="0-10"/>system to complete training and certification;</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="11" slineno="0-11" level="1">requires an individual who sells radon mitigation or vents a radon mitigation system to <ln numlevel="1" lineno="12" slineno="0-12"/>complete training and certification;</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="13" slineno="0-13" level="1">requires an employer to ensure that an employee performing radon mitigation work <ln numlevel="1" lineno="14" slineno="0-14"/>obtains required training and certification before performing that work; and</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="15" slineno="0-15" level="1">authorizes the division to exempt an individual from certification requirements if the <ln numlevel="1" lineno="16" slineno="0-16"/>individual works under direct one-to-one supervision of a certified professional.</hl></hp><moni numlevel="1" lineno="17" slineno="0-17" display="none">Money Appropriated in this Bill:</moni><moniNone lineno="18">None</moniNone><oc numlevel="1" lineno="19" slineno="0-19">Other Special Clauses:</oc><ocNone lineno="20">None</ocNone><sa numlevel="1" lineno="21" slineno="0-21">Utah Code Sections Affected:<saent numlevel="1" lineno="22" slineno="0-22"><snhead>ENACTS:</snhead><sn num="58-55-308.2" src="code" uid="C58-55-S308.2_2026050620260506" buid="6" sort="58 55 03080220260506" numlevel="1" lineno="23" slineno="0-23"><bold>58-55-308.2</bold>, Utah Code Annotated 1953</sn></saent></sa></lt><enacthead lineno="24"/><enact numlevel="1" lineno="25" slineno="0-25">Be it enacted by the Legislature of the state of Utah:</enact><bdy><bsec buid="6" num="58-55-308.2" type="enact" src="code" uid="C58-55-S308.2_2026050620260506" sort="58 55 03080220260506" numlevel="1" lineno="26" slineno="1-1" sn="1"><section numlevel="1" lineno="27" slineno="1-2" number="58-55-308.2" type="enact"><secline lineno="26">Section 1. Section <bold>58-55-308.2</bold> is enacted to read:</secline><catline lineno="27"><bold>58-55-308.2<parens/>. Radon mitigation.</bold></catline><subsection ssid="6-3" dnum="_-o:1-i" numlevel="1" lineno="28" slineno="1-3" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1" placement="noreturn"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1000" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(1)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="11" groupid="8" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">This section applies to:</amend><subsection ssid="6-4" dnum="_-o:a-i" numlevel="1" lineno="29" slineno="1-4" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1001" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="14" groupid="10" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">a person that is licensed to install, repair, maintain, clean, or replace a radon <ln numlevel="1" lineno="30" slineno="1-5"/>mitigation system; and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="6-15" dnum="_-o:b-i" numlevel="1" lineno="31" slineno="1-6" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1002" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="51" groupid="35" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">an individual who sells radon mitigation or vents a radon mitigation system.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="6-6" dnum="_-o:2-i" numlevel="1" lineno="32" slineno="1-7" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1003" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(2)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="20" groupid="14" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">A person described in Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="58-55-308.2(1)">(1)</xref> shall:</amend><subsection ssid="6-7" dnum="_-o:a-i" numlevel="1" lineno="33" slineno="1-8" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1004" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="23" groupid="16" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">before beginning the work described in Subsection (1)(a) or (1)(b), <marker pairid="56">re</marker>ceive training <ln numlevel="1" lineno="34" slineno="1-9"/>and certification in accordance with rules the commission makes with the <ln numlevel="1" lineno="35" slineno="1-10"/>concurrence of the director and in accordance with Title 63G, Chapter 3, Utah <ln numlevel="1" lineno="36" slineno="1-11"/>Administrative Rulemaking Act; and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="6-8" dnum="_-o:b-i" numlevel="1" lineno="37" slineno="1-12" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1005" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="26" groupid="18" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">ensure that an employee performing work described in Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="58-55-308.2(1)(a)">(1)(a)</xref> or <xref depth="4" refnumber="58-55-308.2(1)(b)">(1)(b)</xref> <ln numlevel="1" lineno="38" slineno="1-13"/>first receives training and certification as the division requires by rule made in <ln numlevel="1" lineno="39" slineno="1-14"/>accordance with Title 63G, Chapter 3, Utah Administrative Rulemaking Act.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="6-16" dnum="_-o:3-i" numlevel="1" lineno="40" slineno="1-15" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1006" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(3)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="55" groupid="38" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">The division may exempt an individual from the certification requirements described in <ln numlevel="1" lineno="41" slineno="1-16"/>Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="58-55-308.2(2)">(2)</xref> who works under the direct supervision of a certified individual in <ln numlevel="1" lineno="42" slineno="1-17"/>accordance with Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="58-55-308.2(2)">(2)</xref>.</amend></subsection></section></bsec><bsec buid="8" type="uncod" untype="effdate" src="uncod" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" langlock="true" numlevel="1" lineno="43" slineno="2-1" sn="2"><section type="uncod" untype="effdate" display="false" src="uncod"><secline lineno="43">Section 2.  <bold>Effective Date.</bold></secline><sectionText lineno="44"><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1" groupid="1" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="both">This bill takes effect on <effdate uid="code" date="5/6/2026">May 6, 2026</effdate>.</amend></sectionText></section></bsec></bdy><foot><rev><tm>2-13-26 10:00 AM</tm></rev></foot></leg>